The paper focuses on neural architecture search (NAS) for image classification tasks, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves optimizing the architecture using gradient-based methods, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of convolution kernels is a common technique in deep learning, which is a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the reduction of memory and computation requirements, which is relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
